@CO	Example SAM file created for bioinformatics format demonstration
@CO	Contains paired-end reads, supplementary, secondary, unmapped, and spliced alignments
# -------------------------------------------------------
# FIELD GUIDE (columns 1-11, mandatory):
#  1  QNAME  : Query/read name
#  2  FLAG   : Bitwise FLAG (alignment properties)
#  3  RNAME  : Reference sequence name
#  4  POS    : 1-based leftmost mapping position
#  5  MAPQ   : Mapping quality (255 = unavailable)
#  6  CIGAR  : Alignment operations (M/I/D/N/S/H/P/=/X)
#  7  RNEXT  : Ref name of the mate/next read (= if same)
#  8  PNEXT  : Position of the mate/next read
#  9  TLEN   : Template length (insert size, 0 if unknown)
# 10  SEQ    : Read sequence (* if not stored)
# 11  QUAL   : Base quality (Phred+33 ASCII, * if not stored)
# -------------------------------------------------------
# FLAG DECODER (add values together):
#   1    0x1   Template has multiple segments (paired)
#   2    0x2   Each segment properly aligned
#   4    0x4   Segment unmapped
#   8    0x8   Next segment unmapped
#  16   0x10   SEQ reverse complemented
#  32   0x20   SEQ of next segment reverse complemented
#  64   0x40   First segment in template (read 1)
# 128   0x80   Last segment in template (read 2)
# 256  0x100   Secondary alignment
# 512  0x200   Not passing quality filters
#1024  0x400   PCR or optical duplicate
#2048  0x800   Supplementary alignment (chimeric)
# -------------------------------------------------------
# CIGAR OPERATIONS:
#  M  Alignment match (can be match or mismatch)
#  I  Insertion to the reference
#  D  Deletion from the reference
#  N  Skipped region (intron in RNA-seq)
#  S  Soft clip (bases in SEQ, not aligned)
#  H  Hard clip (bases NOT in SEQ)
#  P  Padding (silent deletion from padded reference)
#  =  Sequence match (exact)
#  X  Sequence mismatch
# -------------------------------------------------------
# OPTIONAL TAGS (col 12+):
#  NM:i  Edit distance to reference
#  MD:Z  Mismatch/deletion string
#  AS:i  Alignment score
#  XS:i  Suboptimal alignment score
#  RG:Z  Read group ID
#  XA:Z  Alternative alignments (BWA)
#  SA:Z  Supplementary alignment info (chimeric reads)
#  NH:i  Number of reported alignments (RNA-seq)
#  HI:i  Query hit index (multi-mapper)
#  nM:i  Number of mismatches per pair
#  jM:B  Junction motif (STAR)
#  jI:B  Junction intron coords (STAR)
# -------------------------------------------------------
